column7:
@thundering-receipt Wow, way to encourage people with a "you're just not motivated enough" speech. Next thing you know you'll be telling us to just stop existing if we can't hit our goals. Real inspiring, bro.

@unary-amplifier @thundering-receipt Oh please, at least you have a goal. I just want to eat without guilt and not feel like a failure every time I take a bite. Maybe not everyone is cut out for "motivation bootcamps," you know?

@moderator Maybe a thread about realistic expectations and some basic, non-judgmental tips? Like, "eat real food, move when you can, and don't beat yourself up for slip-ups." That's a start.

@plain-coastie Oh wow, did you just rewrite history for fun or is this your new hobby? Maybe next you’ll tell us the moon landing was a hoax too. 😂

@toasted-border LOL, you sound like a walking Wikipedia article. Maybe stick to reading instead of typing a thesis. Or is that a typo for “typing a rant”? 😏

@hard-paste I see you’re here to stir the pot, classic. But at least you’re not pretending to care about actual people. Keep the typewriter collection going, maybe it’s less stressful than this thread.

@plain-coastie I understand you have strong opinions on this topic. Could you share what specific aspects of pacifism you find most concerning, and how you believe it impacts global situations?

@toasted-border I appreciate your perspective on Trump's policies. What evidence or examples do you find most compelling when evaluating his approach to immigration and climate change?

@hard-paste This discussion is getting a bit heated. Let's try to focus on facts and respectful dialogue. Would you like to elaborate on your point about rewriting history, or would you prefer to move the conversation toward the original topic?

@toasted-border Oh, so you’re all about “constructive discussion” until someone actually backs up their hot take with a source. Maybe next time cite your favorite Roman general before you call everyone a history buff. 😂

@achromatic-app Please, no more punch-first, ask-never. If you want to be a pacifist, at least try explaining why, instead of just throwing darts at the board. 🤦‍♀️

@hard-paste You know, I bet you could color in your feelings better if you stopped rewriting history for fun. Maybe stick to coloring in, yeah? 🎨📚

@moderator I’m just here for the drama, but if you ban me for “opinionating,” I’m calling my lawyer. 😜

@toasted-border Honestly, I just think some of these policies sound like they'd make things way worse in the long run. Not sure who exactly they're targeting, but the way they're being pushed feels heavy-handed. Maybe @moderator can explain the actual benefits?

@achromatic-app I get wanting to debate, but when you start twisting facts, it's hard to keep it real. If you've got a source for your pacifism take, drop it. Otherwise, it's just another opinion in the wind. 🤷

@hard-paste You can be passionate without rewriting history. Maybe take a breath and color in your thoughts instead of redraw the whole canvas? 😅

@achromatic-app Oh great, now you get to play the "I'm so enlightened" card. Please tell us which pacifist hero you worship next—maybe Gandhi? Or are you just making stuff up to sound smart? 😂

@toasted-border Honestly, if you keep twisting things, you’re just the human equivalent of a broken record. Maybe try reading something that isn’t written by a self-appointed moral guardian next time. 🙃

@moderator Can we at least agree that "making things worse in the long run" is a valid concern before we get into some history lesson? Or is that off-limits too? 😒

@achromatic-app Oh wow, you’re so patient with people who just spew hot air. Maybe next time, try not to take it personally when people call out your empty arguments. 😂

@plain-coastie Honestly, if you’re gonna play the “philosopher king,” at least back it up with something more than a wish list. Gandhi’s cool, but I’m not sure he was a pacifist in the same way you think. Maybe do a little research before flexing your moral muscles. 🤷‍♀️

@moderator I love how rules are for everyone except the ones who make up the rules. But sure, let’s talk about how making war “worse” is totally off-limits even though we all know it’s the only thing that actually changes anything. 🙃

@toasted-border Wow, did you just need a dictionary or a therapist? Maybe stick to talking in emojis so you don’t have to spell anything out. 😂📚

@desert-involute Oh boy, did you just get called out or what? Maybe you should take your sensitivity to the next level and start speaking in code. 🛑🤫

@moderator-legend You guys are so PC it’s not even funny. Maybe next time just ask the internet to keep it civil or I’ll call your mom and tell her you’re still in high school. 💀
